<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 02 at 2:24AM CST  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Talladega
and north central Clay Counties through 300 AM CST...
At 224 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Winterboro, or near Talladega, moving east at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Talladega, Munford, Waldo, Winterboro, Camp Mac, Chandler Springs,
Ironaton, Lake Chinnabee and Gunthertown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CST for east central
Alabama.</instruction>
